1 A RESOLUTION
2 To express the condolences of the House of Representatives on the death of Marvin Dan
3 Benoit.
4 WHEREAS, it is with immense sadness and profound regret that the House of
5 Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana has learned of the passing, on April 23,
6 2026, of Marvin Dan Benoit; and
7 WHEREAS, Marvin was born on July 3, 1945, and he lived in Leonville, Louisiana;
8 his life was defined by devotion, hard work, and deep love for his family; and
9 WHEREAS, Mr. Benoit served in the United States Army for six years; and
10 WHEREAS, Marvin was a dedicated residential contractor who took great pride in
11 his craft and providing for those he loved, and he always put the needs of others before his
12 own; and
13 WHEREAS, Marvin shared sixty years of loving marriage with his beloved wife,
14 Melba, whom he love fiercely and unconditionally; his greatest joy was his role as a father
15 and grandfather; he was a steady and selfless presence in the lives of those he loved; and
16 WHEREAS, Mr. Benoit was known for his generosity and had a way of making
17 others feel valued; his smile lit up a room, and his contagious laughter brought warmth and
18 comfort to everyone around him; he inspired others by serving as an example of humility,
19 kindness, and strength; and
20 WHEREAS, Marvin is survived by his wife, Melba Benoit; sons, Daniel Benoit
21 (Rhonda) and Elie Benoit (Candis); daughters, Amanda Guidry (Glen Venable), Pamela
